<h2>
    Introduction to Smallmouth Bass Fishing in Oregon
</h2>
<p>
    Smallmouth bass, known for their fighting spirit and feisty nature, are not native to Oregon, but they have thrived in its rivers and reservoirs since being introduced. Today, they are a prime target for anglers due to their abundance, size, and the excitement they bring to every catch. Oregon’s diverse freshwater systems, especially around Eugene, make it an ideal destination for smallmouth enthusiasts.
</p>
